Note that I have no idea where the FP will go in the future, that is beyond me and often times defies reason. I just wanted to write down what appears to be another great story in NFT-land, and one that I hope replicates for hard-working creators over and over again.
When I bought in yesterday (finally) there were still around 9k pieces to be sold and I definitely didn't expect it to sell out, but I'm very happy for the artist that it did.

I've been following the artist for a few months:
- solo artist from Japan
- hand drawn 10,000 skulls
- launched collection in August 2021 at mostly 0.01 per piece
- very little traction (a few sales per day) until yesterday when someone with reach gave the project visibility
I'm really enjoying watching the @kawaiiskull_nft  day unfold. Participating in these moments for artists are the ones that give me such optimism about the space.
